38294>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
38294>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
38294>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
38297>>>
38297>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38297>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38297>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38297>>>        Case Begin
38297>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38299>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38299>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38299>>>                Case Break
38300>>>                
38300>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38303>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38303>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38303>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38303>>>                Case Break
38304>>>                
38304>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38307>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38307>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38307>>>                Case Break
38308>>>                
38308>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38308>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38308>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38308>>>                  
38308>>>        Case End
38308>>>
38308>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38308>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38308>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38309>>>
38309>>>    End_Procedure
38310>>>
38310>>>End_Object
